<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1513,2008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1765,1791]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is dedicated to the late Valerie Todd Davies, a pioneering Australian arachnologist; name in genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1513,2008]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,151,537]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1837,1863]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Grall &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Grall &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[332,563,1837,1863]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Micropoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daviesae" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis box="[332,563,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Micropoda daviesae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[574,692,1837,1863]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[574,692,1837,1863]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
may be recognised by the following combination of characters: Males (
<figureCitation box="[236,370,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1855,1879]" captionTargetBox="[167,1407,203,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[167,1420,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Micropoda daviesae gen. &amp; spec. nov. holotype male from New Britain. 47–49 Right palp, mirrored (47 prolateral, 48 ventral, 49 retrolateral); 50 Proximal part of cymbium and tegulum showing embolus base and alveolus pocket; 51 RTA, ventro-distal; 52 Tip of embolus and embolic apophysis, retrolateral. AP—alveolus pocket, bT—big tooth at RTA, C—conductor, dlA—dorso-lateral apex of RTA, E—embolus, EA—embolic apophysis, RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis, S—spermophor, sT—small tooth at RTA, ST—subtegulum, TR—tegular ridge, vlA—ventro-lateral apex of RTA." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911181/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 47–52</figureCitation>
): 1. RTA proximally arising from tibia, with 2 lateral apices, a large medial tooth and a small additional tooth (
<figureCitation box="[344,427,1909,1936]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1855,1879]" captionTargetBox="[167,1407,203,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[167,1420,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Micropoda daviesae gen. &amp; spec. nov. holotype male from New Britain. 47–49 Right palp, mirrored (47 prolateral, 48 ventral, 49 retrolateral); 50 Proximal part of cymbium and tegulum showing embolus base and alveolus pocket; 51 RTA, ventro-distal; 52 Tip of embolus and embolic apophysis, retrolateral. AP—alveolus pocket, bT—big tooth at RTA, C—conductor, dlA—dorso-lateral apex of RTA, E—embolus, EA—embolic apophysis, RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis, S—spermophor, sT—small tooth at RTA, ST—subtegulum, TR—tegular ridge, vlA—ventro-lateral apex of RTA." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911181/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
), 2. Embolus arising from tegulum at 5-o’clock-position, filiform and apically coiled and 3. Embolic apophysis arising from embolus in 10-o’clock-position, running parallel to and with similar width of embolus up to their tip. Females (
<figureCitation box="[485,616,1981,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,561,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-220@13.[151,1436,561,1718]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 53–57. Micropoda daviesae gen. &amp; spec. nov. female paratype from New Britain, copulatory organ. 53 Epigyne, ventral; 54, 56 Vulva (54 dorsal, 56 lateral); 55, 57 Schematic course of internal duct system (55 dorsal, 57 lateral). EF—epigynal field, EP—epigynal pocket, FD—fertilization ducts, FW—first winding of internal duct system, GA—glandular appendages, LL—lateral lobes, SP—spermatheca, Wi—window of first winding." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911187/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 53–57</figureCitation>
