<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,150,1004]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Copulatory organ as in diagnosis (
<figureCitation box="[581,712,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,561,1718]" captionTargetId="figure-220@13.[151,1436,561,1718]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 53–57. Micropoda daviesae gen. &amp; spec. nov. female paratype from New Britain, copulatory organ. 53 Epigyne, ventral; 54, 56 Vulva (54 dorsal, 56 lateral); 55, 57 Schematic course of internal duct system (55 dorsal, 57 lateral). EF—epigynal field, EP—epigynal pocket, FD—fertilization ducts, FW—first winding of internal duct system, GA—glandular appendages, LL—lateral lobes, SP—spermatheca, Wi—window of first winding." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911187/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 53–57</figureCitation>
). Epigynal field wider than long with fusion bubbles situated antero-medially. Lateral lobes kidney-shaped and distinct. Copulatory orifices situated medio-anteriorly. Internal duct system longer than wide. Glandular appendages short and straight, extending only in anterior half of internal duct system. Fertilization ducts situated medio-posteriorly, short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,150,1004]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Colouration in ethanol (
<figureCitation box="[472,606,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 82–97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-19@19.[151,1436,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 82–97. Heteropodinae gen. &amp; spp. nov., habitus (dorsal and ventral, respectively). 82–85 Borniella parva gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 86–89 Menarik kecil gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 90–93 Micropoda davisae gen. &amp; spec. nov.; 94–97 Tiomaniella ladam gen. &amp; spec. nov. (82–83, 86–87, 90–91, 94–95 holotype male, 84–85, 88–89, 92–93, 96–97 female paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911203" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911203/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 92–93</figureCitation>
): Prosoma yellowish, anterior part with two wide, brown stripes running medially to ALE, medially brown with brown stripes, posterior part medially with semi-circular yellow pattern, lateral and latero-posterior margin brown. Fovea with longitudinal reddish-brown stripe. Sternum pale yellow. Opisthosoma yellowish-grey with brown spots, medially with four brown dots, in front of spinnerets white spot, ventral part yellowish-grey, medially grey, laterally brown. Chelicerae reddish-brown with two dark longitudinal brown stripes, retrolaterally with brown spot. Palps yellowish-brown. Legs yellowish-brown; Fe medially and proximally with brown band; Ti proximally with brown band.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,150,1004]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,502,834,860]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Variation. Females (n=4).</emphasis>
TL 5.5–6.7; PL 2.6–3.3, PW 2.4–3.2, AW 1.4–1.9; OL 2.9–3.4, OW 2.0–2.3. Measurements leg I: total length 8.20–10.80, Fe 2.20–3.00, Pa 1.10–1.50, Ti 2.20–2.90, Mt 1.90–2.50, Ta 0.80–1.00. Spination: legs: Ti 
<date box="[364,481,906,933]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1016-01" valueMax="1016-03-31" valueMin="1016-01-00">I–III 1016</date>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
